version_unique_justification: The project uses semantic versioning for its releases
version_tags_justification: The project uses git tags to identify versions: https://github.com/etr/libhttpserver/releases
release_notes_justification: Non-trivial release notes file in repository: <https://github.com/etr/libhttpserver/blob/master/ChangeLog>.
release_notes_vulns_justification: No reported security vulnerabilities so far.
report_responses_justification: The authors always reply as soon as possible to all requests, either via github or via email.
enhancement_responses_justification: The authors always reply as soon as possible to all requests, either via github or via email.
vulnerability_report_response_justificat: no vulnerabilities reported in the last 6 months
build_justification: The system uses autotools to build ( https://github.com/etr/libhttpserver/blob/master/configure.ac ).
build_floss_tools_justification: All the software the code depends to be built and executed on is FLOSS (https://github.com/etr/libhttpserver/blob/master/configure.ac). Travis build showcase this ( https://travis-ci.org/etr/libhttpserver )
test_justification: The codebase is tested using liblittletest ( https://github.com/etr/liblittletest/ ). Demonstration of tests ( https://github.com/etr/libhttpserver/tree/master/test )
test_invocation_justification: All tests are invoked through "make check" ( https://github.com/etr/libhttpserver/blob/master/test/Makefile.am ) as showcased in travis ( https://travis-ci.org/etr/libhttpserver ).
test_most_justification: Line coverage is current at 96% (achieved through both unit and integ tests). Pull requests are checked not to lower this value and cover the whole new code that is introduced. Coverage is steadily moving up. This visible through codecov ( https://codecov.io/gh/etr/libhttpserver )
test_policy_justification: As explained in our contribution guidelines (https://github.com/etr/libhttpserver/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md) every change goes through pull-request. Every pull-request is built within travis that runs all the tests and re-performs coverage.
tests_are_added_justification: Every functionality is tested as part of the build process. As part of the checks in the pull-request (required to introduce the functionality), it is checked that the code-coverage is not reduced.
tests_documented_added_justification:
Every functionality is tested as part of the build process. As part of the checks in the pull-request (required to introduce the functionality), it is checked that the code-coverage is not reduced.
This is documented in our contribution guidelines: https://github.com/etr/libhttpserver/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md
warnings_justification: The project is built with "-Wall" option within travis on both gcc and clang (https://travis-ci.org/etr/libhttpserver)
warnings_fixed_justification: Warnings are notified by travis and addressed by maintainers
warnings_strict_justification: The project is built with "-Wall" and pedantic enabled on both gcc and clang on travis (https://travis-ci.org/etr/libhttpserver).
know_secure_design_justification: The maintainer is trained in writing secure code (as a developer on enterprise applications).
know_common_errors_justification: The maintainer is trained in writing secure code (as a developer on enterprise applications).
crypto_published_justification: The software uses gnutls to support https.
crypto_call_justification: The software uses gnutls to support https.
crypto_floss_justification: The software uses gnutls to support https (which is FLOSS).
crypto_keylength_justification: This is supported by gnutls and managed transparently by libhttpserver
crypto_password_storage_justification: The library doesn't manage user credentials storage
static_analysis_common_vulnerabilities_j: Both cppcheck and coday are configured to do so. Cppcheck is executed when building on travis at every commit ( https://travis-ci.org/etr/libhttpserver ). Codacy is performed at every commit as well ( https://app.codacy.com/project/etr/libhttpserver/ )
static_analysis_fixed_justification: Static analysis tools are re-performed at every commit (on all branches) thus resulting in full check of both the master branch and all the pull requests. This is driven through travis ( https://travis-ci.org/etr/libhttpserver ) and codacy ( https://app.codacy.com/project/etr/libhttpserver/ ). In case of failure, the maintainers are notified of the failure and will act immediately.
static_analysis_often_justification: Static analysis tools are re-performed at every commit (on all branches) thus resulting in full check of both the master branch and all the pull requests. This is driven through travis ( https://travis-ci.org/etr/libhttpserver ) and codacy ( https://app.codacy.com/project/etr/libhttpserver/ ). In case of failure, the maintainers are notified of the failure and will act immediately.
dynamic_analysis_unsafe_justification: Builds using ASAN, TSAN, MSAN, LSAN and UBSAN are performed at every travis execution ( https://travis-ci.org/etr/libhttpserver ).
dynamic_analysis_enable_assertions_justi: The builds using ASAN, TSAN, MSAN, LSAN and UBSAN ran all the unit tests with coverage above 95% that exercises also all the assertion within the codebase ( https://travis-ci.org/etr/libhttpserver ).
dynamic_analysis_fixed_justification: Dynamic analysis tools are re-performed at every commit (on all branches) thus resulting in full check of both the master branch and all the pull requests. This is driven through travis ( https://travis-ci.org/etr/libhttpserver ). In case of failure, the maintainers are notified of the failure and will act immediately.
test_continuous_integration_justificatio: This is achieved through travis that runs tests on every build (on every commit) - ( https://travis-ci.org/etr/libhttpserver )
discussion_justification: GitHub supports discussions on issues and pull requests.
hardened_site_justification: Found all required security hardening headers.
